The paper deals with the problem of recovering a low-rank matrix from linear measurements using an over-parameterized model. This problem is closely related to topics in machine learning, optimization, and signal processing. Specifically, the paper proposes a gradient descent algorithm for matrix recovery, which can be viewed as a non-linear matrix factorization problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper involves some theoretical analysis of the algorithm's convergence and performance, which may fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
